        <body>
            <pb n="1R"/>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>Berlin Marquette County Wisconsin</placeName>
            </p>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <date>October 9<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1851</date>
            </p>
            <p>
                <addressee>Rev Isaac Leeser</addressee>
                <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
            </p>
            <p>Rev Sir</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">You will undoubtedly be pleased<lb/> to hear, that in this
                    <placeName>Backwood Country</placeName><lb/> there <sic>where</sic> assembled on
                the Day of atone-<lb/>ment a few of our people to praise the Lord<lb/> on high. We
                meet to the number of thirteen<lb/> at the house of <persName>Mr Kensel</persName>,
                who lives about<lb/> twenty miles north of this Place, on Lands<lb/> belonging to
                the late <sic>menomienee</sic> purchase<lb/> so you will, that the Land are not
                even<lb/> sold yet to actual settlers, and yet in that wilder_<lb/>ness where a few
                of Gods <sic>choosen</sic> ones assembled<lb/> to sing praises to his name. We had
                everything<lb/> to make the Day pass off, according to ancient usage<lb/> There was
                    <add>ספיח</add> and <add>שופר</add> belonging to <persName>Mr
                Kusel</persName><lb/> and there was also in our small congregation a<lb/>
                <add>כהן</add> and a <add>לוי</add> and everything went off to the
                satis=<lb/>faction of every body present. Knowing that you<lb/> take a great
                    <sic>intress</sic> in everything concerning<lb/> our holy faith, I send you this
                Lines thinking<lb/> that <sic>the</sic> will be read by you with pleasure</p>
            <pb n="1V"/>
            <p>and if you should see fit to publish the<lb/> same in the next number of the
                Occi-<lb/>dent, you will oblige very much your<lb/> most obd. Servant</p>
            <p rend="indent(4)">
                <persName role="author">M. Markwell</persName>
            </p>
        </body>
    </text>
